Eight domestic animals were Saturday night slashed to death by unknown assailants at the Kapoloin Catholic parish in Kericho. When faithfuls arrived at the church compound in Ainamoi constituency, the animals carcasses which had multiple deep machete wounds were strewn all over the place. The shocking incident led to the cancelation of the regular Sunday sermon at the parish, which was officially opened in June 2014. Police, and church leaders led by Fr Valleyves Makhola, are currently holding a meeting to investigate the matter with the aim of unmasking the animal killers. Case of people attacking animals have been on the rise in Kericho in the last one year. More to follow. Avoid becoming a victim of Fake News. Subscribe to the Standard Group SMS service by texting 'NEWS' to 22840.